{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_62","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' PR_COMMENTS.md\"","aggregated_output":"This change resolves the actionable Uberon part of issue `#3464` by obsoleting the four unused temporal-boundary terms under the life-cycle branch:\n\n- `UBERON:0035943` obsolete life cycle temporal boundary\n- `UBERON:0035944` obsolete life-death temporal boundary\n- `UBERON:0035945` obsolete start of life cycle\n- `UBERON:0035946` obsolete start of neonate stage\n\nRationale:\n\n- The issue discussion concluded that these classes are vestiges of over-formalized 0D temporal modeling in Uberon.\n- They are not referenced elsewhere in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n- Where a reasonable stage-level replacement exists, I added conservative `consider` tags:\n  - `UBERON:0035944` -> `UBERON:0000071 ! death stage`\n  - `UBERON:0035946` -> `UBERON:0007221 ! neonate stage`\n- I did not add a replacement for `UBERON:0035945` because the start of a life cycle is taxon-dependent in Uberon; a single cross-taxon replacement would be misleading.\n- I did not move `UBERON:0000104 ! life cycle` or `UBERON:0000105 ! life cycle stage` to a different upper-level parent here. In this local ontology file there is still no clear local `process` superclass to target, and the issue thread indicates that this part depends on unresolved COB-side upper-level alignment.\n\nChecklist completed:\n\n- Read the imported issue context and comments.\n- Inspected the current stanzas for `life cycle`, `life cycle stage`, and all four temporal-boundary terms using `obo-grep.pl`.\n- Confirmed the four temporal-boundary IDs were not used elsewhere in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n- Checked stage replacement candidates before adding `consider` tags.\n- Edited via `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow and committed only `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n\nValidation:\n\n- Verified the resulting git diff only changed the four intended term s